    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - CAB FEATURES - RADIO (ENTERTAINMENT), SPEAKERS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0825811">
        <title>RADIO (ENTERTAINMENT), SPEAKERS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825846">entertainment radio function diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0825846" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08258A1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Entertainment Radio Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ENTERTAINMENT RADIO</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The entertainment radio is permanently installed and operates from the vehicle 12 volt system using an
                external antenna and speakers.
            </para>
            <para>The radio is supplied switched battery voltage to allow it to operate when the key is on. The radio
                also receives battery voltage to provide power from the radio memory.
            </para>
            <para>Panel light voltage is supplied to the radio for backlighting.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
